Setup suggestions for Raspberry Pi 3

- Flash Raspbian Lite to SD card
- For wired network insert ethernet cable
- Insert SD card and boot
- Login: pi / raspberry
- Set new user password: passwd
- Set new root password: sudo passwd
- For WiFi: sudo nano /etc/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.conf
  Add to end of file:
  network={
    ssid="YOUR_SSID"
    psk="YOUR_PASSWORD"
  }

- sudo reboot, login and check connection with ping -c3 http://www.google.com
  NOTE: may require a couple of minutes to find connection after reboot

- To flip screen 180 degrees:
  sudo nano /boot/config.txt
  Add to end of file:
  lcd_rotate=2
- Save and sudo reboot

- sudo apt-get update
- sudo apt-get upgrade
- sudo apt-get dist-upgrade

- sudo raspi-config
  -> 3  Boot options
  -> B2 Console Autologin
- Finish and reboot

- sudo apt-get install xserver-xorg xinit xterm xdg-utils
- sudo reboot

- sudo nano /etc/X11/xorg.conf
  Add to end of file (disable monitor blanking):
  Section "ServerFlags"
       Option         "blank time" "0"
       Option         "standby time" "0"
       Option         "suspend time" "0"
       Option         "off time" "0"
   EndSection
   Section "InputClass"
       Identifier            "Keyboard Setting"
       MatchIsKeyboard       "yes"
       Option                "XkbOptions" "ctrl:swapcaps"
   EndSection

- Test X11 with xinit, then exit (with exit)

- Download and install Processing:
  - curl https://processing.org/download/install-arm.sh | sudo sh

- Install git:
  sudo apt-get install git
  cd ~
  git clone https://github.com/PiScore/PiScore

- Test Processing in X11, and set preferences
  xinit
  processing
  - Uncheck welcome message on startup
  - File -> Preferences
    - Check "Increase maximum available memory to:" 512MB -> Enter to save
  - Quit Processing

- cp /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc ~/.xinitrc
- nano ~./xinitrc
  Add before last command:
  processing-java --sketch=/home/pi/PiScore/sketches/launcher/ --run

- nano ~/.profile
  Add to end of file:
  exec startx
